492
00:31:52,610 --> 00:31:56,915
I really didn't want… to be disliked.

493
00:31:57,582 --> 00:31:58,983
So I ended up

494
00:31:59,484 --> 00:32:04,589
spending my life
trying not to get too close to people.

495
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:08,259
But… after coming here,

496
00:32:08,826 --> 00:32:10,995
I learned that everyone here

497
00:32:11,062 --> 00:32:14,599
has hardships and different experiences
in their lives.

498
00:32:14,666 --> 00:32:17,001
I was really encouraged by that.

499
00:32:17,502 --> 00:32:19,737
If I hadn't come here…

500
00:32:20,872 --> 00:32:24,309
…I definitely wouldn't have considered
coming out.

501
00:32:25,443 --> 00:32:26,611
Because I came here,

502
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:28,179
I was able

503
00:32:28,913 --> 00:32:30,248
to write a letter.

504
00:32:31,149 --> 00:32:33,084
I wrote to my parents.

505
00:32:34,018 --> 00:32:35,486
Maybe…

506
00:32:36,287 --> 00:32:38,556
I hope, with this letter I wrote,

507
00:32:39,490 --> 00:32:41,125
I'll be able to

508
00:32:42,293 --> 00:32:45,596
give hope or courage to someone else.

509
00:32:46,097 --> 00:32:50,768
It's going to take some time,
but please let me read it aloud here.

510
00:32:52,804 --> 00:32:53,972
Let's hear it.

511
00:33:00,244 --> 00:33:02,013
"Dear Dad and Mom,

512
00:33:02,513 --> 00:33:04,482
I'm sorry for this sudden letter."

513
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:06,417
"I picked up my pen today

514
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:09,554
because there is something
I really want to tell you."

515
00:33:10,121 --> 00:33:11,222
"I'm gay."

516
00:33:11,723 --> 00:33:14,726
"As a man, I feel attracted to men."

517
00:33:15,226 --> 00:33:19,297
"It's not anyone's fault,
and it's not like there was any trigger."

518
00:33:19,797 --> 00:33:23,101
"It's simply that,
just as Dad fell in love with Mom,

519
00:33:23,167 --> 00:33:25,403
I naturally feel attracted to people."

520
00:33:26,104 --> 00:33:29,307
"It just so happens
to be with someone of the same sex."

521
00:33:29,807 --> 00:33:33,177
"To me, it's nothing else.
That's all it is."

522
00:33:33,945 --> 00:33:38,249
"I've known that I was gay
since I was a little boy."

523
00:33:38,750 --> 00:33:41,519
"But you two always said

524
00:33:41,586 --> 00:33:44,389
that as long
as I was healthy and 'normal,'

525
00:33:45,456 --> 00:33:47,425
that was all that mattered."

526
00:33:47,925 --> 00:33:53,297
"I just felt so sorry for not being
the 'normal' person you expected."

527
00:33:53,931 --> 00:33:57,435
"And I lived believing
that keeping it to myself

528
00:33:57,502 --> 00:34:00,972
was what would make our family happy."

529
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:04,542
"But as I grew older,

530
00:34:05,143 --> 00:34:07,111
every time I came back home,

531
00:34:07,178 --> 00:34:10,815
I noticed you two seemed a little smaller
each time."

532
00:34:11,382 --> 00:34:17,588
"And I realized that we didn't have
much time left as a family,

533
00:34:18,089 --> 00:34:23,394
and I started to question
whether it was right to keep it a secret."

534
00:34:23,461 --> 00:34:27,932
"And I decided to tell you
that I was gay."

535
00:34:29,567 --> 00:34:32,703
"You both sacrificed your lives
to raise me,

536
00:34:33,204 --> 00:34:35,940
and telling you this
would sound ungrateful."

537
00:34:36,007 --> 00:34:41,612
"The thought that you might not forgive me
terrified me."

538
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:45,083
"But then I met nine friends."

539
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:51,389
"Their ages, nationalities,
and backgrounds were all so different."

540
00:34:51,456 --> 00:34:54,125
"We laughed and cried together,

541
00:34:54,192 --> 00:34:56,194
shared a lot of experiences,

542
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:58,830
and learned and grew together."

543
00:35:00,431 --> 00:35:02,633
"If I hadn't met these friends,

544
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:05,336
I would have run away forever."

545
00:35:05,837 --> 00:35:09,140
"And I wouldn't have been able
to write this letter."

546
00:35:12,543 --> 00:35:16,747
"Dad, you've always been busy with work
since I was a kid."

547
00:35:16,814 --> 00:35:19,851
"You were away from early morning
to late at night."

548
00:35:19,917 --> 00:35:22,520
"You were strict and always angry,

549
00:35:22,587 --> 00:35:25,323
so I hated you when I was a kid."

550
00:35:26,057 --> 00:35:29,594
"But when I became an adult
and started working every day myself,

551
00:35:30,161 --> 00:35:34,298
I finally realized
your strength and greatness."

552
00:35:34,365 --> 00:35:36,434
"Now I respect you deeply."

553
00:35:38,136 --> 00:35:42,507
"Mom, I love you for your kindness,

554
00:35:42,573 --> 00:35:46,878
and I'm trying my best
to be kind to others in my own way."

555
00:35:47,411 --> 00:35:51,816
"Thank you so much for giving birth to me
and raising me with so much love."

556
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:55,686
"I want you to understand
what 'normal' happiness means to me,

557
00:35:55,753 --> 00:35:58,923
even though it's a little different
from everyone else's."

558
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:01,826
"And if you can forgive me,

559
00:36:01,893 --> 00:36:05,296
I want to walk through life
with both of you as a family again."

560
00:36:07,131 --> 00:36:10,735
"Thank you so much for everything.
From Tomoaki."

561
00:36:15,072 --> 00:36:16,607
I'm sure they'll understand.

562
00:36:18,075 --> 00:36:21,012
- Sorry for taking up your time.
- No, it's fine.

563
00:36:22,146 --> 00:36:23,614
Thank you for reading it.

564
00:36:24,415 --> 00:36:25,349
Thank you.

565
00:36:33,624 --> 00:36:36,394
Can I have one final hug before I go?

566
00:36:37,995 --> 00:36:38,963
Thank you.

567
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:46,237
You were the most cheerful one
and always made everyone smile.

568
00:36:46,304 --> 00:36:48,639
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

569
00:36:48,706 --> 00:36:50,575
- Wishing you the best.
- Mm.

570
00:36:51,442 --> 00:36:54,645
- Are you okay, Ryuki? You got this.
- I'm okay. It's okay. It's okay.

571
00:36:54,712 --> 00:36:56,814
- Take care coming out.
- Yeah.

572
00:36:56,881 --> 00:36:58,282
- You too, Ryuki.
- Mm.

573
00:36:59,016 --> 00:37:00,318
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

574
00:37:00,384 --> 00:37:03,454
- I know it's hard, but…
- Mm. I'll be okay.

575
00:37:03,955 --> 00:37:07,258
Tomoaki. Thank you.

576
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:10,995
Thank you for choosing me
to run the coffee truck with you.

577
00:37:11,495 --> 00:37:13,197
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

578
00:37:13,264 --> 00:37:14,398
Thank you.

579
00:37:15,333 --> 00:37:16,934
- Good luck.
- Good luck.

580
00:37:17,435 --> 00:37:19,403
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

581
00:37:23,541 --> 00:37:25,176
Don't forget about me, okay?

582
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,211
I wanna forget you, but I can't.

583
00:37:28,479 --> 00:37:30,314
If you forget me,
I'll show up at your place.

584
00:37:30,381 --> 00:37:31,449
What?

585
00:37:31,515 --> 00:37:32,617
Bye-bye.

586
00:37:34,619 --> 00:37:36,687
Oops, I hit something.

587
00:37:37,188 --> 00:37:39,590
Still so loud until the very end.

588
00:37:47,832 --> 00:37:50,901
- Oh, that letter absolutely got me.
- It was such a wonderful letter.

589
00:37:50,968 --> 00:37:52,803
Especially when he first came
to the Green Room.

590
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:53,738
He was very sensitive.

591
00:37:53,804 --> 00:37:56,407
He was very sensitive,
but he became the life of the party.

592
00:37:56,474 --> 00:37:57,575
Yeah.

593
00:37:57,642 --> 00:37:59,777
He's become
someone who can write a letter like that.

594
00:37:59,844 --> 00:38:01,879
He had a great look on his face.

595
00:38:01,946 --> 00:38:05,283
Whether it's in a letter, in words,
or just through a conversation,

596
00:38:05,349 --> 00:38:08,552
expressing your gratitude and feelings
is really important.

597
00:38:08,619 --> 00:38:10,054
It's important.

598
00:38:12,089 --> 00:38:13,057
Well then…

599
00:38:15,159 --> 00:38:16,260
I'll go now.

600
00:38:18,462 --> 00:38:20,031
The reason I came here,

601
00:38:20,531 --> 00:38:24,402
I went through a really painful experience
in my last relationship.

602
00:38:24,468 --> 00:38:27,204
I couldn't trust anyone anymore.

603
00:38:27,772 --> 00:38:30,775
And I couldn't take the next step
into another relationship.

604
00:38:31,275 --> 00:38:33,744
But after coming here,

605
00:38:33,811 --> 00:38:37,348
I saw Izaya and William really nurture
their love for each other.

606
00:38:37,415 --> 00:38:38,549
<i>It was great.</i>

607
00:38:39,050 --> 00:38:41,218
<i>And heard everyone</i>
<i>talk about who they like,</i>

608
00:38:41,285 --> 00:38:42,787
<i>what they're struggling with,</i>

609
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:45,323
<i>and their own views on romance.</i>

610
00:38:45,389 --> 00:38:48,492
Even though I couldn't find romance here
for myself,

611
00:38:48,559 --> 00:38:52,063
I was able to realize
that not everyone out there is bad.

612
00:38:52,129 --> 00:38:55,966
I really felt that here
and meeting everyone.

613
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,435
Good.

614
00:38:57,501 --> 00:39:00,871
I think I can move on
to another relationship.

615
00:39:00,938 --> 00:39:01,939
That's good.

616
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:04,742
So I'm okay with romance now.

617
00:39:04,809 --> 00:39:05,910
- That's good.
- Yeah.

618
00:39:07,011 --> 00:39:08,813
And about coming out,

619
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:14,385
at first, I really didn't feel like
talking about it in front of everyone.

620
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:16,520
I thought it would be pointless
to talk about it.

621
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:19,223
But after running the coffee truck
with Jobu,

622
00:39:19,724 --> 00:39:21,859
I felt like I could try talking about it.

623
00:39:23,894 --> 00:39:25,296
And after talking about it,

624
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:28,599
I realized that there were other people
who were struggling too.

625
00:39:28,666 --> 00:39:31,902
Like when Jobu's mom brought <i>oden,</i>

626
00:39:32,603 --> 00:39:37,241
I saw that love… could still exist
even after coming out.

627
00:39:37,308 --> 00:39:39,844
Both Hiroya and Jobu showed that.

628
00:39:41,345 --> 00:39:44,382
Yeah. So I'm actually excited,

629
00:39:44,448 --> 00:39:47,251
although it's weird to say
that I'm excited about coming out.

630
00:39:47,318 --> 00:39:51,889
- Mm.
- I'm curious to see how my dad will react.

631
00:39:51,956 --> 00:39:55,493
I've come to see coming out
in a positive light.

632
00:39:55,559 --> 00:39:56,394
Wow.

633
00:39:57,061 --> 00:40:01,799
And even if… things don't go
the way I hoped,

634
00:40:03,567 --> 00:40:05,636
I still have everyone I met here.

635
00:40:07,371 --> 00:40:12,843
So I believe
I can… proudly tell… my father

636
00:40:13,477 --> 00:40:14,979
about my real self.

637
00:40:18,649 --> 00:40:22,153
- You've become stronger. You've grown.
- Yeah.

638
00:40:24,955 --> 00:40:26,023
I'll do my best.

639
00:40:29,226 --> 00:40:31,996
- Thank you.
- I'm rooting for you.

640
00:40:34,098 --> 00:40:35,232
Thank you so much.

641
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,838
What you said at the end

642
00:40:41,472 --> 00:40:42,840
was so positive.

643
00:40:42,907 --> 00:40:44,375
- I was surprised.
- Really?

644
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:48,412
Yeah. You're completely different…
from when you first came here.

645
00:40:49,747 --> 00:40:50,581
Yeah.

646
00:40:50,648 --> 00:40:52,316
I'll keep you all updated.

647
00:40:52,383 --> 00:40:55,519
- Make sure to hear about my love life too.
- I will. Of course I will.

648
00:40:56,020 --> 00:40:57,354
- Take care.
- See you.

649
00:40:57,421 --> 00:40:58,956
- Take care.
- Bye.

650
00:41:00,391 --> 00:41:01,525
I don't wanna go.

651
00:41:02,059 --> 00:41:04,595
- You don't want to?
- Ryu! Good luck!

652
00:41:05,296 --> 00:41:07,131
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

653
00:41:09,099 --> 00:41:09,934
I love you guys.

654
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,836
- <i>So cute!</i>
- <i>That was cute!</i>

655
00:41:11,902 --> 00:41:15,039
- We love you too.
- <i>That was a killer move.</i>

656
00:41:27,451 --> 00:41:29,386
Ryuki is really young,

657
00:41:29,453 --> 00:41:33,123
and he's also been deeply hurt in love.

658
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:37,761
His family situation was a part
of what was really holding him back,

659
00:41:38,262 --> 00:41:39,230
but he's changed.

660
00:41:39,296 --> 00:41:41,298
I think having a place to return to

661
00:41:41,365 --> 00:41:44,335
when things don't go
the way you had hoped for

662
00:41:44,401 --> 00:41:46,737
is a wonderful treasure for Ryuki.

663
00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:49,907
I think the confidence
to come out with pride

664
00:41:49,974 --> 00:41:51,575
and have the support of friends

665
00:41:51,642 --> 00:41:54,445
is the greatest treasure he gained
in the Green Room.

666
00:41:56,914 --> 00:41:57,915
Well then,

667
00:41:58,582 --> 00:42:00,251
I guess it's my turn.

668
00:42:06,090 --> 00:42:07,291
But, like,

669
00:42:08,125 --> 00:42:10,027
I feel so clear and free now.

670
00:42:10,094 --> 00:42:11,629
- Mm.
- Mm.

671
00:42:12,663 --> 00:42:13,597
I…

672
00:42:14,765 --> 00:42:17,768
had two really fun months.

673
00:42:19,470 --> 00:42:24,975
After I decided to come here
and be honest about my feelings…

674
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:30,314
Mm. I worked really hard in my own way.

675
00:42:32,082 --> 00:42:34,051
And I had friends who faced me.

676
00:42:37,021 --> 00:42:39,223
I'm truly excited
about what's ahead in life.

677
00:42:39,924 --> 00:42:41,859
So I want to thank everyone

678
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:44,895
and leave here with a smile.

679
00:42:46,030 --> 00:42:47,865
<i>He's got a great look on his face.</i>

680
00:42:48,532 --> 00:42:52,469
Well,
now that it's just the two of you left,

681
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:55,773
I want to say I'm rooting for you,

682
00:42:55,839 --> 00:42:59,009
and whatever the outcome is,
I'm on your side.

683
00:43:06,050 --> 00:43:06,984
All right.

684
00:43:11,488 --> 00:43:12,790
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

685
00:43:13,791 --> 00:43:15,159
- Oh, you're skinny.
- Shut up.

686
00:43:16,660 --> 00:43:17,595
Thank you.

687
00:43:18,562 --> 00:43:20,197
- It was fun.
- Mm-hmm.

688
00:43:21,498 --> 00:43:23,233
- See you.
- See you.

689
00:43:23,300 --> 00:43:24,168
Thank you.

690
00:43:24,735 --> 00:43:25,569
I love you guys.

691
00:43:25,636 --> 00:43:29,406
There it is! Hey, hey,
you're copying Ryuki! Thanks!

692
00:43:29,473 --> 00:43:30,608
Thanks.

693
00:43:30,674 --> 00:43:31,508
Goodbye.

694
00:43:32,009 --> 00:43:34,144
<i>He has a calm, bright look on his face.</i>

695
00:43:34,211 --> 00:43:36,146
<i>He looks so much better.</i>

696
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:48,058
I think Hiroya will meet
a really wonderful person after this.

697
00:43:48,125 --> 00:43:52,630
Yeah. He's just not very good
at expressing his feelings,

698
00:43:52,696 --> 00:43:56,133
but he genuinely cares about people
and his friends.

699
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:59,570
- He's a kind person.
- I'm glad that came across at the end.

700
00:43:59,637 --> 00:44:02,606
This is a confidence-building experience
for Hiroya.

701
00:44:03,107 --> 00:44:05,309
He'll be able to build
proper relationships

702
00:44:05,376 --> 00:44:06,710
in other communities too.

703
00:44:06,777 --> 00:44:09,647
It made me feel encouraged
not to give up on relationships.

704
00:44:09,713 --> 00:44:12,182
Yeah, these days it's so easy
to cut people out of your life

705
00:44:12,249 --> 00:44:15,386
when they get troublesome
and move on to a different world.

706
00:44:15,452 --> 00:44:18,989
It made me feel that being involved
with people is really wonderful.

707
00:44:40,711 --> 00:44:42,479
I have something to say.

708
00:44:43,013 --> 00:44:44,581
Go ahead.

709
00:44:46,016 --> 00:44:48,218
You wrote me a letter on my first day,

710
00:44:48,919 --> 00:44:50,154
and you picked me again

711
00:44:50,220 --> 00:44:52,456
to work the coffee truck with you
the second time.

712
00:44:52,956 --> 00:44:55,092
To be honest, at first,

713
00:44:56,627 --> 00:44:58,762
hmm, I was cautious around you.

714
00:44:59,730 --> 00:45:01,198
We'd only just met,

715
00:45:01,865 --> 00:45:05,169
but you wrote in your letter
that you were drawn to me.

716
00:45:05,235 --> 00:45:08,772
So I was worried that if I showed you
a different side of me,

717
00:45:09,473 --> 00:45:12,509
you might not feel the same way about me.

718
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:15,212
I didn't want to disappoint you.

719
00:45:17,014 --> 00:45:18,649
But in the middle of that,

720
00:45:19,149 --> 00:45:20,884
I don't know when it happened,

721
00:45:21,919 --> 00:45:24,755
I found myself
wanting to have breakfast with you.

722
00:45:25,422 --> 00:45:26,824
When I ran the coffee truck,

723
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:29,026
I found myself wondering
what you had for lunch

724
00:45:29,526 --> 00:45:32,496
and what kind of day you were having.

725
00:45:33,564 --> 00:45:36,300
I wondered if you slept well
the night before.

726
00:45:37,034 --> 00:45:38,902
More and more, mm,

727
00:45:39,403 --> 00:45:41,972
I found myself thinking about you.

728
00:45:43,173 --> 00:45:45,943
Well, the first time
we ran the coffee truck,

729
00:45:46,009 --> 00:45:47,644
I didn't enjoy it at all.

730
00:45:48,512 --> 00:45:53,650
So I was convinced that I would never have
that kind of relationship with you.

731
00:45:54,485 --> 00:45:58,689
That's why
I didn't even want to… accept it at first.

732
00:45:59,690 --> 00:46:03,761
But… after I started feeling that way,

733
00:46:03,827 --> 00:46:06,230
the Sapporo trip came around.

734
00:46:07,731 --> 00:46:10,501
And I picked you. That was because,

735
00:46:11,068 --> 00:46:14,605
hmm, I felt like
I couldn't leave you alone.

736
00:46:14,671 --> 00:46:15,873
Uh-huh?

737
00:46:15,939 --> 00:46:18,575
I felt like I wanted to take you with me.

738
00:46:19,810 --> 00:46:24,047
But we also had the overnight date
after that, right?

739
00:46:25,315 --> 00:46:28,752
That's when I started

740
00:46:29,753 --> 00:46:34,591
to doubt our relationship even more,
to be honest.

741
